     You can control some  ways  of  printing  the status window. It's
possible the add the time, the date and your name to the printout. You
can also tell the printer to eject the page after printing.
@endnode

@node QuizPrefs
                          ===============
                          =             =
                          =  QuizPrefs  =
                          =             =
                          ===============


==================================================================
=  +-% Correct/Wrong-++----Tries----++----Wait for continue---+  =
=  |                 ||             ||                        |  =
=  | O 0% C / 100% W || O 10 tries  || O Never                |  =
=  | O 10% C / 90% W || O 20 tries  || O After a wrong answer |  =
=  | O 20% C / 80% W || O 30 tries  || O Always               |  =
=  | O 30% C / 70% W || O 40 tries  |+------------------------+  =
=  | O 40% C / 60% W || O 50 tries  |                            =
=  | O 50% C / 50% W || O 60 tries  |                            =
=  | O 60% C / 40% W || O 70 tries  |                            =
=  | O 70% C / 30% W || O 80 tries  |                            =
=  | O 80% C / 20% W || O 90 tries  |                            =
=  | O 90% C / 10% W || O 100 tries |                            =
=  | O 100% C / 0% W ||             |                            =
=  +-----------------++-------------+                            =
==================================================================


     Imagine that you're starting  a  test  of  30  questions with the
minor and the major third as  the selected intervals. Your %Correct is
respectively 90% and 70%. The %Wrong  is  then 10% and 30%. This means
that 1/4 (7 tries) of the  questions  should  be about the minor third
and 3/4 (21 tries) about the  major  third.  The remaining 2 tries are
chosen randomly amongst the selected  intervals. So far, everything is
alright.
     Let's now take %Correct of 100%  and  80%.  The %Wrong is then 0%
and 20%. This means  however  that  no  questions  (0 tries) should be
asked about the minor  third  and  that  all  the questions (30 tries)
should be about the major third. You  can  see that this is not a good
way of testing because you'll never rehearse the minor third any more.
     So I decided to divide  the  number  of  tries into two parts. One
part that will test the wrong  intervals  and  one part that will test
the correct intervals (for  rehearsing  the  acquired knowledge). As a
standard 30% (9 tries) will be  reserved  for the correct part and 70%
(21 tries) will be reserved for the wrong part.
     Let's take the %Correct of before :  100% for the minor third and
80% for the major third. The  %Wrong  is  0%  and 20%. For the correct
part 5/9 (5 tries) of the questions  will handle about the minor third
and 4/9 (4  tries)  about  the  major  third.  For  the  wrong part no
questions (0 tries) about the  minor  third  and all the questions (21
tries) about the major third. The  total of tries is thus respectively
5 tries and 25 tries.
     This division line in between  the wrong and the correct part can
be  controlled   by  the   '% Correct/Wrong'  selector.  Normally  you
shouldn't change this feature.

     The number of tries can be changed in the 'Tries' selector.

     When you answer a question you can ask the computer to wait until
you tell him to  continue.  In  this  waiting  mode  you can press the
interval buttons. You will hear the requested interval played with the
last generated root. This is  very  useful  for comparing intervals to
check what went wrong if you made a mistake.
@endnode

@node SoundPrefs
                          ================
                          =              =
                          =  SoundPrefs  =
                          =              =
                          ================


                       =====================
                       =  +--Duration---+  =
                       =  |             |  =
                       =  | O Short     |  =
                       =  | O Normal    |  =
                       =  | O Long      |  =
                       =  | O Very long |  =
                       =  +-------------+  =
                       =====================


     You can change the length of the interval here. When the interval
is being played successively you will hear each note in half the time.
This ensures that the duration  of  the  whole  interval will stay the
same for whatever type of interval.
@endnode

@node ResetConfig
                      =========================
                      =                       =
                      =  Reset configuration  =
                      =                       =
                      =========================


     When you select this all  the  display  will reset itself to PAL-
Hires 640x256, all the windows  will  be  closed  except for the about
window and every preference items will be reset to its initial state.
     You can get the same  effect  by deleting the EarTrainer.cfg file
in the S: directory.
@endnode

@node SaveConfig
                       ========================
                       =                      =
                       =  Save configuration  =
                       =                      =
                       ========================


     This forces  the  computer  to  save  the  configuration  on that
moment. You can use this  for  example  if  you disabled the saving at
quitting time and if you  changed  something in the configuration that
you want to keep.
@endnode

@node ExitConfig
                   ================================
                   =                              =
                   =  Save configuration at exit  =
                   =                              =
                   ================================


     Normally the eartrainer saves the  configuration at exit. You can
disable this here.
@endnode

@node ClearStatus
                          ==================
                          =                =
                          =  Clear status  =
                          =                =
                          ==================


     It's possible to  clear  the  contents  of  the  status window by
pressing on the 'clear' gadget  or  by  selecting this menu item. When
you cleared it by accident, don't  panic because this only happened to
the work copy in the  memory  of  the  computer.  To restore the saved
status select 'Set  save  path'  and  just  press  'Set  path'  in the
requester. When the computer asks  you  if  he  has to save the status
contents in memory say no and the status will be restored from disk.
@endnode

@node PrintStatus
                          ==================
                          =                =
                          =  Print status  =
                          =                =
                          ==================


     When you select this menu item  or  press the 'Print' gadget, the
status contents will be sent to your printer. Be sure that the printer
is activate and on-line. You can  change  some parameters in the print
preferences window.
@endnode

@node SaveStatus
                          =================
                          =               =
                          =  Save status  =
                          =               =
                          =================


     This forces the computer  to  save  the  status  contents on that
moment.
@endnode

@node PathStatus
                         ===================
                         =                 =
                         =  Set save path  =
                         =                 =
                         ===================


     The   status   contents    are    save    in    a   file   called
'EarTrainer.status'.  With  this  funtion  you  can  select  in  which
directory this file should written or  read.  This it's enables you to
have several status-files.
@endnode

@node ExitStatus
                      =========================
                      =                       =
                      =  Save status at exit  =
                      =                       =
                      =========================


     Normally the eartrainer saves  the  status  contents at exit. You
can disable this here.
@endnode

