@node Enhancements
                      =========================
                      =                       =
                      =  Future enhancements  =
                      =                       =
                      =========================


     You will be able to  define  a  little  melody for each interval.
This melody can be played at wish  and will be transposed to match the
root of the last played interval.  This  will make the memorisation of
the intervals easier.
     Instead of the predefined computer sound,  it will be possible to
choose an IFF or a RAW sample to play the intervals with.
     It will be possible to display the status window in graphics.
     I'm thinking about localising and about adding an AREXX-port. I'd
like to receive some comment on  this  : Are these additions needed or
just  a  freebie?  If  some   could   send  some  information  an  the
implementation of AREXX, I will be very grateful.

    -- IMPORTANT --
     If you have some other ideas, don't  hesitate to write me. I will
have look at them and  if  they're  any  good  I'll  add  them  to the
next version.
@endnode

